        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=5420&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Verant+%22moons%22+us%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">From the offical EQ/Luclin website:</P><P>"The moon of Luclin is in perfect balance -- one side bathed forever in light, and the other steeped in darkest night. The earliest arrivals felt an eerie and disturbing presence when approaching the Twilight between the two areas. Those not native to the moon quickly learned to avoid these dangerous lands. Ironically, it is said that those of good and honest nature made their homes in the darkness, and those of a darker nature chose the light."</P><P>Ever watch the moon in Norrath?  It keeps the same face towards Norrath at all times, just as Earth's moon does.  It has an orbit of one day instead of about a month, but this is not unreasonable.</P><P>Now the problem.  How can "one side bathed forever in light, and the other steeped in darkest night" if it is keeping the same side facing Norrath at all times?  Again, keeping one face of a moon facing the planet it's orbiting at all times would mean it is behaving just like Earth's moon.  Since this is the case, also like Earth's moon, every 'side' of it would eventually be facing the sun as it completed its orbit.  Therefore, there would be no permanently dark and permanently light sides.</P><P>(And let me clarify something for those of you who are still having trouble with this concept.  "The dark side of the moon" that is commonly refered to is actually the side of the moon that can't be seen from Earth.  Actual darkness has nothing to do with it.)</P><P>The conclusion that can be drawn from all this is:  The design team at Verant never got past the 5th grade.  Which explains why a lot of other things work the way they do in Norrath as well.</P><P><IMG src="http://members.spree.com/funngames/qazjax/manapump.jpg"></P><P>Edited by - Qazjax on 06/18/2001  09:35:48</font></td>
      </tr>

