        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">> Ever watch the moon in Norrath?  It keeps <BR>> the same face towards Norrath at all <BR>> times, just as Earth's moon does.  </P><P>There's a real simple reason for this: Texture memory. If they actually had a rotating, dynamic, spinning moon in game, it'd take a lot more memory to display.</P><P>So, basically, forming any kind of "scienctific" conclusion based on what you observe in game is going to be nothing more than idle amusement. it doesn't mean anything.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
