        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">The moon does not rotate.  The world is not heliocentric but Norrath-centric.  The sun revolves around Norrath.  The speed of sun and moon are the same, with the sun separated from the moon by a distance we know as the "day".  The area of the moon that the sun's light hits is its light side, the side the sun's light does not reach is the dark side.  </P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
